def: To be of importance. [Obs.]Which to deny concerns more than avails. Shak.

The conversion of nutriment into the fluid or solid substanceof the body, by the processes of digestion and absorption, whether inplants or animals.Not conversing the body, not repairing it by assimilation, butpreserving it by ventilation. Sir T. Browne.
Of no legal force or effect, incapable of confirmation orratification; null. Cf. Voidable, 2. Void space (Physics), a vacuum.
Turned upside down from its proper position; inverted;reversed.
Cutting at right angles. Orthotomic circle (Geom.), that circlewhich cuts three given circles at right angles.
Capable of bending or yielding; apt to yield; compliant.Another compliable mind. Milton.The Jews . . . had made their religion compliable, and accemodated totheir passions. Jortin.
Of or pertaining to the hippocampus.
The act of eventuating or happening as a result; the outcome.R. W. Hamilton.
A deserted condition. [R.] "The desertness of the country."Udall.
